episodes.title: Brook's Hard Struggle the Difficult Path to Becoming a True Crewmate?
episodes.plot: Brook tries to help his new nakamas because he fears that otherwise he will be dispensed, but Robin tell him her story of Water 7 and he recovers his confidence.

episodes.title: Halfway Through the Grand Line Arrival! The Red Line
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Pirates are about to reach the Red Line but a terrible storm delays them. Log Pose is pointing downwards and the crew needs more information to get to Gyojin Island.

episodes.title: Hatred of the Straw Hat Crew Enter Iron Mask Duval
episodes.plot: Camie and Pappag introduce themselves to the Straw Hats, who then later find out that their fishman friend has been kidnapped by Iron Mask Duval and the Macro Gang.

episodes.title: The Fated Reunion! Save the Imprisoned Fishman
episodes.plot: The mysterious Duval gets excited when the crew that rescued Camie turns out to be the Straw Hat Pirates.

episodes.title: Tragedy! The Truth of the Unmasked Duval
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Pirates do battle with the Flying Fish Riders and Macro Fishman Pirates. The stakes rise when Duval reveals himself, and exactly who his grudge is against: Sanji.

episodes.title: Explosion! The Sunny's Super Secret Weapon Gaon Cannon
episodes.plot: Duval reveals that he was once a small-time bandit until Sanji's wanted poster came to light. Since then he hid his face with the iron mask until he could get revenge on Sanji.

episodes.title: Gyojin-tou o Mezashite Jouriku: Sabaody Shotou
episodes.plot: With the Flying Fish Riders taken care of, the Straw Hats rest as Hatchan treats them to the promised takoyaki.

episodes.title: Bougyaku! Sabaody no Shihaisha Tenryuubito
episodes.plot: After landing on the Sabaody Archipelago, the Straw Hats begin searching for a man Hatchan knows who can coat their ship, so they can continue onto Fishman Island.

episodes.title: Arata na Rival Shuuketsu! 11-nin no Choushinsei
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Pirates fight and defeat some bounty hunters who want their bounty.

episodes.title: Hyouteki wa Camie!! Semaru Hitosaraiya no Mashu
episodes.plot: Departing from Shakky's Rip-off Bar, Luffy's group attempt to search for Rayleigh but is distracted by the Sabaody Park. Zoro is disrespectful to Saint Charlos, causing him to be shot at.

episodes.title: Camie o Sukue: Shotou ni Nokoru Ankoku no Rekishi
episodes.plot: Duval and his crew arrive on the Archipelago and start gathering the Straw Hats up to bring them to the Human Auctioning House, where the kidnappers have brought Camie.

episodes.title: Time Limit: Human Auction Kaimaku
episodes.plot: The human auction finally begins, and it is only then that the Straw Hats discovered that their mermaid friend is being sold off at Grove 1.

episodes.title: Tekken Sakuretsu! Auction o Buttsubuse
episodes.plot: The auction continues, but Saint Charlos arrives and ruins the Straw Hats' plan to buy Camie back by placing an exorbitant bid on her.

episodes.title: Dai Panic! Auction Kaijou no Shitou
episodes.plot: After Luffy punches Charlos, the guards begin to attack the Straw Hats, and most of the observers, except for Charlos' family, Kid and Law's crews, evacuate.

episodes.title: Taishou Kizaru Ugoku! Souzen Sabaody Shotou
episodes.plot: Sengoku dispatches Admiral Kizaru to defend the honor of the Celestial Dragons at Sabaody Archipelago.

episodes.title: Houimou o Toppa Seyo! Kaigun Tai Sannin no Senchou
episodes.plot: Luffy, Law and Kid's crews join the fight and defeat the rest of the Marines outside the Auction House. The three captains promise to meet and fight in the New World.

episodes.title: Roger to Rayleigh: Kaizoku Ou to Sono Migiude
episodes.plot: Upon arriving back at Shakky's Bar, Silvers Rayleigh reveals to the Straw Hats that he was the first mate of the legendary Gol D. Roger and also reveals the truth about his crew's dismissal.

episodes.title: Kaihi Fukanou!? Taishou Kizaru no Kousoku no Keri
episodes.plot: Admiral Kizaru appears at the Archipelago and demonstrates his mysterious light abilities, before taking on the Supernova, Basil Hawkins, whilst Urouge and X Drake fight a Pacifista.

episodes.title: Attouteki! Kaigun no Sentou Heiki Pacifista
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Pirates fight one of the Pacifistas, and while it does not have Kuma's Devil Fruit powers, it is still able to withstand their strongest attacks.

episodes.title: Saranaru Kyouteki Arawaru! Masakari Katsuida Sentoumaru
episodes.plot: The Straw Hat Pirates combine their strongest attacks to defeat the Pacifista, but are exhausted after the battle.

episodes.title: Taishou Kizuru no Moukou Mugiwara Ichimi Zettaizetsumei!
episodes.plot: Usopp and Brook's attempt to attack Kizaru and save Zoro's life failed.

episodes.title: Kesareta Nakama-tachi: Mugiwara Ichimi Saigo no Hi
episodes.plot: Sentomaru reveals that Kuma has the ability to make people fly through the sky to far away places.

episodes.title: Jidaigeki Tokubetsu Hen: Luffy Oyabun Futatabi Kenzan
episodes.plot: In an alternate universe set in Edo period Japan, the Mikoshi (portable shrine) race is about to take place, the winner of which receives Beli1,000,000, and Boss Luffy and his friends recruit Franky to build them a mikoshi.

episodes.title: Jidaigeki Tokubetsu Hen: Yabure! Thriller Shoukai no Wana
episodes.plot: Robin reveals Brook's past to Luffy and his friends, and decide to help him. Brook is captured by Thriller LTD, but Luffy and Zoro arrive to help him escape.

episodes.title: Jouriku! Danshi Kinsei no Shima Amazon Lily
episodes.plot: Having been hit by Kuma, Luffy is teleported to an unknown island.

episodes.title: Isoge! Nakama-tachi no Moto e: Nyougashima no Bouken
episodes.plot: It is revealed that Luffy is on Amazon Lily, an island populated entirely by the Kuja tribe of women warriors.

episodes.title: Minna Meromero! Kaizoku Jotei Hancock
episodes.plot: Luffy decides to leave the island, reunite with his crew and defeat the enemies who had overpowered them earlier, and is determined to borrow a ship.

episodes.title: Senaka ni Kakusareta Himitsu: Souguu Luffy to Hebihime
episodes.plot: Boa Hancock's ship reaches Amazon Lily and she returns to her palace.

episodes.title: Hijou no Sabaki! Ishi ni Sareta Margaret!!
episodes.plot: Luffy looks at Boa Hancock's back and notes that he has seen what was on it before. Hancock tries, but fails to turn him to stone with her powers when he mistakes her Mero Mero no Mi abilities for Foxy's Noro Noro Beam.

episodes.title: Luffy Daikusen! Hebi Shimai no Haki no Chikara!!
episodes.plot: Luffy is challenged to battle Boa Marigold and Boa Sandersonia in the Amazon Lily arena with the spectators calling for Luffy to be executed.

episodes.title: Nouryoku Zenkai Battle!! Gomugomu Tai Hebihebi
episodes.plot: Luffy activates Gear Second and is currently taking the lead.

episodes.title: Hancock no Kokuhaku: Shimai no Imawashiki Kako
episodes.plot: Hancock decides to test Luffy by giving him an ultimatum: either he gets a ship so he can leave the island while the girls remain statues or she changes them back and Luffy finds another way to the archipelago.

episodes.title: Ace o Sukue! Arata na Mokutekichi wa Daikangoku
episodes.plot: Following a party, Luffy learns from Nyon that Hancock is a Shichibukai, and that they have been called together as the Marines is launching an all-out offensive on Whitebeard.

episodes.title: Koi wa Hurricane! Meromero Hancock
episodes.plot: When Nyon visits Hancock, she deduces her illness and when she mentions Luffy wishes to see her, this causes Hancock to get up and speak with him.

episodes.title: Nakama-tachi no Yukue: Tenkou no Kagaku to Karakurijima
episodes.plot: Nami and Franky story, where they landed and what did they do.

episodes.title: Nakama-tachi no Yukue: Kyochou no Shima to Momoiro no Rakuen!
episodes.plot: Sanji and Chopper story, where they landed and what did they do.

episodes.title: Nakama-tachi no Yukue: Shima o Tsunagu Hashi to Shokujin Shokubutsu
episodes.plot: Robin and Usopp story, where they landed and what did they do.

episodes.title: Nakama-tachi no Yukue: Negative Princess to Akuma Ou
episodes.plot: Zoro and Brook story, where they landed and what did they do.

episodes.title: Kesshi no Sennyuu! Kaitei Kangoku Impel Down Sennyuu!
episodes.plot: Vice Admiral Garp talked proudly to Ace at Impel Down about some of Luffy's actions, and mentions that they both have the blood of a world class criminal.

episodes.title: Jigoku de Saikai!? Bara Bara no Mi no Jitsuryokusha!
episodes.plot: Hancock turns Domino to stone before she can undergo the body-check, allowing Luffy to escape into the prison.

episodes.title: Yabure! Guren Jigoku: Buggy no Dohade Daisakusen
episodes.plot: Buggy and Luffy fight their way through to the entrance of Level 2 by going through Level 1, Crimson Hell, where the lowest ranking criminals are held.

episodes.title: Kangoku Saikyou no Otoko! Doku Ningen Magellan Toujou
episodes.plot: Hancock and the others finally reach the office of Magellan, a large man who has eaten the Doku Doku no Mi.

episodes.title: Eiga Rendou Special: Ugokidasu Kinjishi no Yabou
episodes.plot: Luffy, Zoro, Usopp, and Sanji arrive on an island called Little East Blue, a smaller version of the East Blue, which is where they met each other.

episodes.title: Eiga Rendou Special: Nerawareta Little East Blue
episodes.plot: Luffy, Sanji, Zoro, and Usopp arrive on the island and go to their favorite places in the East Blue.

episodes.title: Eiga Rendou Special: Amigo Kaizokudan no Moukou
episodes.plot: Largo uses his devil fruit power to create nets from his body and trap Zoro and Sanji.

episodes.title: Eiga Rendou Special: Kessen! Luffy Tai Largo
episodes.plot: After escaping from the net, Luffy knocks Largo far away and goes off to fight him.

episodes.title: Toraware no Ouka Shichibukai! Kaikyou no Jinbee
episodes.plot: Luffy and Buggy find Galdino and together they continue to fight through Level 2 of Impel Down, hounded by both Manticores and Puzzle Scorpions.

episodes.title: Roubanchou Saldeath no Wana: Level 3 Kiga Jigoku
episodes.plot: Luffy, Buggy, and Galdino find themselves on Level 3, a barren floor of extreme heat.

episodes.title: Tokihanatareta Swan! Saikai! Bon Clay
episodes.plot: The prison staff and Hancock finally arrive on the floor where Ace is being held.
